  "texts": [
    "It achieved exceptional results for basic emotions such as joy and sadness (F1-scores of 0.94 and 0.95), followed by a strong performance for anger and fear (both 0.89).",
    "More complex emotional states proved more challenging, with love achieving an F1-score of 0.81 and surprise showing the lowest performance at 0.72.",
    "For mental health conditions, the model achieved the highest performance in detecting anxiety and bipolar disorder (F1-scores of 0.86 and 0.85, respectively) while maintaining robust performance for depression detection (F1: 0.79).",
    "Zero-shot prompting showed notably strong performance in mental health condition detection, particularly for depression and anxiety (F1-scores of 0.70 and 0.74).",
    "However, its performance on emotion classification varied considerably."
